# Angular Component Rules

- Always use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`.
- Use signal APIs: `input()` instead of `@Input()`.
- Use signal APIs: `output()` instead of `@Output()` + `EventEmitter`.
- Use query functions: `viewChild` / `contentChild` instead of decorators.
- Keep components under 150 lines; split UI or logic into smaller units when needed.

```typescript
// BAD
@Input() userName: string = '';
@Output() userSelected = new EventEmitter<User>();
@ViewChild('modal') modal!: ElementRef;
```

```typescript
// GOOD
userName = input<string>('');
userSelected = output<User>();
modal = viewChild<ElementRef>('modal');
```

When generating components, include:
- `standalone: true`
- `changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
